{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place orange segments and garlic in mixing bowl then chop <b>Turbo\/1 sec\/1-2 times<b>. Scrape down sides and lid of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add vinegar, mustard, honey, oil, salt and pepper in mixing bowl then mix <b>10 sec\/speed 4<b>.","Place pork chops in a large dish and pour marinade over. Cover then set aside in fridge for at least 2 hours.","Towards the end of marinating time, heat oil in a griddle pan over a medium heat. Cook pork (reserving marinade) for 12-15 minutes, turning once until cooked as desired with distinctive griddle lines on meat. Meanwhile, place reserved marinade in mixing bowl.","Add sugar and water then, without measuring cup, reduce <b>5-7 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b> until sauce has thickened to desired consistency.","Serve garnished with orange segments and a choice of salad and\/or potatoes."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["1 orange, peeled and pith removed, in 8 segments (approx. 100 g), plus extra segments for garnish","1 garlic clove","1 Tbsp cider vinegar","1 Tbsp wholegrain mustard","3 Tbsp runny honey","1 tsp olive oil, plus extra for cooking","¼ tsp fine sea salt, or to taste","2 pinches ground black pepper, or to taste","4 pork chops (approx. 150 g each)","½ tsp dark brown muscovado sugar","2 Tbsp water"]}],"id":"r140008","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-gbZeDb1HXc0\/XZQxs6gtgXI\/AAAAAAAAcxw\/8Lh8IB4AEg4-SrvQk6APFci99cXsD4PEwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_yo-pcWRTUjuM2pUI.png","title":"Pork Chops with Orange","publishedAt":"2017-01-09T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"48.2 g","fat":"11.3 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"11.7 g","calories":"1426 kJ \/ 341 kcal"},"usefulItems":"cling film, dish, skillet or griddle pan, refrigerator, hob","basicInfo":["easy","25m","2h 25m","4 portions"]}